def: The third tone of the scale. See Mediant.
The quality or character of an amateur.
An Irish measure of two feet in length.
An American fresh-water fish (Ictiobus, or Carpiodes,cyprinus); -- called also carp sucker, sailfish, spearfish, andskimback.
A female sexton; a sexton's wife.

A gambling or lottery device consisting of a wheel which isspun horizontally, articles or sums to which certain marks on itscircumference point when it stops being distributed according tovarying rules.
Tasteful; in a tasteful, agreeable manner.
Grand and dignified; in grand style.
That one of the two primary divisions of the vegetable kingdomwhich contains the phanerogamic, or flowering, plants.

United; connected; associated. "Influence conjoint." Glover.Conjoint degrees (Mus.), two notes which follow each otherimmediately in the order of the scale, as ut and re. Johnson.Conjoint tetrachords (Mus.), two tetrachords or fourths, where thesame note is the highest of one and the lowest of the other; -- alsowritten conjunct.
